X-PIE: Crosslink-Guided Protein Interaction Ensemble Modeling
================================================================================

Version: 1.0
License: MIT
DOI: 10.5281/zenodo.20523994

X-PIE is a computational pipeline for building three-dimensional structural
models of protein-protein complexes from crosslinking mass spectrometry (XL-MS)
data. The method clusters crosslink sites into spatially distinct interaction
interfaces prior to conformational sampling, enabling modeling of multiple
binding modes between protein pairs.


