        ├── Calc_*.pdb
        └── Calc_*.pdb.viols

File Descriptions:
------------------

| File                    | Description                              |
|-------------------------|------------------------------------------|
| *_domains.txt           | Domain boundary definitions              |
| *_linker.txt            | Long disordered region definitions       |
| *_clusters.txt          | Interface state assignments              |
| *_schematic.png         | Crosslink-domain visualization           |
| xlms.tbl                | Distance restraints for XPLOR            |
| refine.py               | XPLOR sampling control script            |
| *-prepare.pdb/psf       | Cleaned structures with rebuilt H atoms  |
| Calc_*.pdb              | Generated structural models              |
| Calc_*.pdb.viols        | Per-model restraint violation reports    |

The Example folder contains the input and output files for all systems described in the manuscript.
================================================================================
8. TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

Problem: Missing PDB files
    Solution: Ensure every protein name in link.dat has a matching <name>.pdb.

Problem: DSSP (mkdssp) not found
    Solution: Install mkdssp and verify it is in your PATH.

Problem: XPLOR not found
    Solution: Set correct paths in x-pie.cfg or ensure xplor is in your PATH.

Problem: PSF generation fails
    Solution: Check that PDB files use standard atom and residue names.
              AlphaFold models usually work without modification.

Problem: Empty or single-state clusters
    Solution: With very few crosslinks, only one interface state may be found.
              This is expected behavior. Verify that NZ atoms exist at the
              specified residue numbers.

Problem: Crosslinked residues lack side chains
    Solution: Rebuild missing side chains using tools such as PDBFixer or
              manual modeling before running X-PIE.


